<h2>Master's Thesis</h2>

<h3>Ergonomic Redesign of a Button Hook for Individuals with Dexterity Impairments</h3>

<p>
This project focused on redesigning a traditional button hook to improve comfort,
grip stability, and usability for individuals with limited hand dexterity.
The design process included needs assessment, CAD modeling, 3D printing,
laser-cut jig fabrication, and user testing.
</p>

